# Project Rules

Cross-agent project memory lives in `.agents/memory/`. Always read it at session start — it holds the most recent user corrections and project state, and wins over anything in `AGENTS.md` or `CLAUDE.md` on conflict.

@.agents/memory/MEMORY.md

## Stable Baseline Rules

For the stable ruleset (git workflow, type safety, serializers, multi-tenancy, etc.):

@AGENTS.md
@CLAUDE.md

## Writing New Rules

When you learn a durable project rule (a correction from the user, a validated non-obvious choice, a project fact with a deadline or stakeholder), write a new file in `.agents/memory/` with YAML frontmatter:

```markdown
---
name: {short name}
description: {one-line description}
type: feedback | project | reference
---

{body with **Why:** and **How to apply:** lines for feedback/project}
```

Then add a one-line entry to `.agents/memory/MEMORY.md` pointing at the new file. See `.agents/memory/README.md` for the full format.

Do not write rules to `CLAUDE.md` or `AGENTS.md` directly — those are stable baselines. Evolving learnings go in `.agents/memory/` so they're visible to Claude Code, Codex CLI, and Cursor at the same time.
